-- China Stocks: China Nonferrous Metal, Hubei Yihua, Zijin Mining
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-12-22T08:08:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-21/shanghai-pudong-bank-zijin-mining-china-equity-preview.html
The  Shanghai Composite Index , which
tracks the bigger of China’s stock exchanges, fell 26.22, or 0.9
percent, to 2,877.90 at the 3 p.m. close. The  CSI 300 Index 
declined 1.1 percent to 3,215.45. Stock symbols are in
parentheses after company names.  China Nonferrous Metal Industry’s Foreign Engineering and
Construction Co.  (000758 CH) added 1.9 percent to 33 yuan after
saying it signed a deal worth 4.9 billion yuan ($736.6 million)
with an Iranian company to build an aluminum smelter with an
annual production capacity of 155,000 metric tons.  Hubei Yihua Chemical Industry Co.  (000422 CH), Asia’s
largest fertilizer producer, rose 0.8 percent to 20.12 yuan, a
fourth day of gains. The company will invest 33 billion yuan in
a coal chemical project in the Xinjiang region during the next
five years, the China Daily said, citing Chairman  Jiang Yuanhua .  Shenzhen Changhong Mold Technology Co.  (300151 CH), a mold
manufacturer, climbed 31 percent from its offer price to 44.49
yuan on the first day of trading in Shenzhen.  Zijin Mining Group Co.  (601899 CH), China’s largest gold
producer, lost 1.4 percent to 8.36 yuan. The 21st Business
Herald reported that the Guangdong provincial government
punished 36 officials including Zijin Mining managers for a
fatal dam collapse in September. Calls to Zijin company
secretary  Zheng Yuqiang  were not answered.  -- Zhang Shidong . Editors: Richard Frost  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
